                <div class="section-body">
                    <h4>What you need to know:</h4>

                    <div class="learning-points">
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Data Packets:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>(a) Understand that data is broken down into packets to be transmitted.</li>
                                    <li>(b) Describe the structure of a packet (Packet Header, Payload, Trailer).</li>
                                    <li>(c) Describe the process of packet switching.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Transmission Methods:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>(a) Describe how data is transmitted from one device to another using different
                                        methods:
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Serial vs Parallel</li>
                                            <li>Simplex vs Half-duplex vs Full-duplex</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>(b) Explain the suitability of each method of data transmission for a given
                                        scenario.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>USB Interface:</strong> Understand the Universal Serial Bus (USB) interface and
