                <div class="section-body">
                    <h4>What you need to know:</h4>

                    <div class="learning-points">
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>The Need for Checks:</strong> Understand the need to check for errors after data
                                transmission and how these errors can occur (interference, data loss, data gain, data
                                change).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Transmission Error Detection:</strong> Describe the processes involved in:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Parity checks (odd and even)</li>
                                    <li>Checksums</li>
                                    <li>Echo checks</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Data Entry Error Detection:</strong> Describe how a <strong>check digit</strong>
                                is used to detect errors in data entry (e.g., ISBNs and barcodes).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>ARQ:</strong> Describe how an Automatic Repeat Query (ARQ) can be used to
                                establish that data is received without error.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Nested Notes Collapsible -->
                    <details class="notes-box">
                        <summary>
                            <h4>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Notes & Guidance</span>
                                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                            </h4>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Parity Check:</strong> Can be a parity bit (byte level) or a parity block
                                    check (checking a block of data). Note that parity checks cannot detect if an even
                                    number of bits have changed (transposition error).</li>
                                <li><strong>ARQ:</strong> Uses <em>positive/negative acknowledgements</em> (ACK/NACK)
                                    and <em>timeouts</em>. If no acknowledgement is received before the timeout, the
                                    data is resent automatically.</li>
                                <li><strong>Check Digits:</strong> Used to spot human error when typing in numbers (like
                                    swapping two digits or missing a digit).</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
