                                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Understand the need for and purpose of encryption when
                                transmitting data (confidentiality).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Methods:</strong> Understand how data is encrypted using:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Symmetric encryption</li>
                                    <li>Asymmetric encryption</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Nested Notes Collapsible -->
                    <details class="notes-box">
                        <summary>
                            <h4>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Notes & Guidance</span>
                                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                            </h4>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Symmetric Encryption:</strong> Uses a single secret key for both encryption
                                    and decryption. Fast, but the key must be shared securely.</li>
                                <li><strong>Asymmetric Encryption:</strong> Uses a pair of keys (Public Key and Private
                                    Key).
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><em>Public Key:</em> Used to encrypt data (available to everyone).</li>
                                        <li><em>Private Key:</em> Used to decrypt data (kept secret by the receiver).
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
